21/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Justice Minister Anton Stankov met with ambassadors from EU member states in Sofia on Monday (21 March), assuring them that key judicial reforms would be finalised by year's end. According to Stankov, the ministry is completing work on a new reform draft law, which would be placed on parliament's agenda by mid-May.
Also Monday, the government announced that it has agreed to buy a 20-year-old frigate from Belgium. The purchase is part of an ongoing effort to modernise the navy to meet NATO standards. (Dnevnik, Mediapool - 21/03/05) 
